Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat
oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and thinly slice @red onion{1}. Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a
large pan over medium heat. Add onion, @sugar{1/2%tsp} (1 tsp for 4), and @salt{}.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender and browned, ~{8-10%minutes}.

In the last minute of cooking, add 1 TBSP @water{} (2 TBSP for 4) and stir until
onion is jammy. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Meanwhile, halve, core, and thinly slice @pear{1}. Roughly chop
@walnuts{1/2%ounce}.

== Toast the Flatbreads ==

Place @flatbreads{2} on a #baking sheet{} and bake on top rack until lightly
toasted, ~{5-7%minutes}. (For 4 servings, divide between two baking sheets; toast
on top and middle racks, swapping rack positions halfway through toasting.)

== Cook the Pear ==

While flatbreads toast, heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in pan used for onion
over medium-high heat. Add pear and cook until softened and slightly browned,
~{2-3%minutes} per side.

== Assemble the Salad ==

In a large #bowl{}, toss @arugula{2%ounce} with half the @balsamic glaze{5%tsp}.
Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} to taste.

== Broil and Finish ==

Remove flatbreads from oven and set broiler to high.

Carefully top flatbreads with @blue cheese dressing{1.5%ounce}, onion,
@Italian cheese blend{1/2%cup}, pear, walnuts, and as many @chili flakes{1%tsp} as
you like.

Return to top rack and broil until cheese is melted, ~{2-3%minutes} (for 4 servings,
broil in batches).

Drizzle flatbreads with as much remaining balsamic glaze as you like. Top with
salad and cut into pieces.

Divide between plates and serve.

